Vice President Prof. Yemi Osinbajo on Thursday promised that the Federal Government will collaborate with the Lagos State University (LASU) on Science, Technology Engineering and Mathematics (STEM). He made this statement at the ongoing grand finale of 23rd convocation of LASU. Osinbajo delivered the convocation lecture on the topic: ‘African Centre of Excellence in Africa: A veritable catalyst for nation building and development. The convocation is graced by the Vice Chancellor of LASU Prof. Lanre Adigun Fagbohun and host Governor Akinwunmi Ambode. Others at the event are former President of Ghana Mr. John Mahama and Chairman Governing Council of LASU Prof. Adebayo Ninalowo.